         <abstract>
            <p>We consider variable stepsize time approximations of holomorphic semigroups on general Banach spaces. For strongly A(θ)-acceptable rational functions a general stability theorem is proved, which does not impose any constraint on the ratios between stepsizes.</p>
          </abstract>
